  "prompt": "Are there any antibiotics that can be purchased over the counter?",
  "response": "In many countries, antibiotics are not available over the counter (OTC) due to concerns about antibiotic resistance and the need for medical oversight in their use. In the United States, for instance, all antibiotics require a prescription from a licensed healthcare provider. \n\nHowever, there are some countries where certain topical antibiotics, like bacitracin or neomycin, can be purchased without a prescription. These are typically used for minor cuts, scrapes, or infections on the skin.\n\nIf you believe you need antibiotics, it's important to consult with a healthcare professional for advice and proper treatment. Self-medicating with antibiotics can lead to misuse and increased resistance, making infections harder to treat in the future.",
